                        <div id="content">
                            <article>
                                <h2>Strawberry Lemonade Concentrate</h2>
                                
                                <div class="recipe-meta">
                                    <div class="recipe-meta-item">‚è±Ô∏è Prep Time: 45 mins</div>
                                    <div class="recipe-meta-item">üî• Processing Time: 15 mins</div>
                                    <div class="recipe-meta-item">üè∫ Yield: 6 pints </div>
                                    <div class="recipe-meta-item">üìÖ Season: Summer</div>
                                </div>

                                <section class="recipe-section">
                                    <h3>Equipment Needed</h3>
                                    <ul class="ingredient-list">
                                                                                                                       <li>1 water-bath canning pot</li>
                                      <li>6 pint jars with new lids and rings</li>
                                      <li>Food processor or blender</li>
                                      <li>Large non-reactive saucepan (stainless steel or enameled)</li>
                                      <li>Thermometer</li>
                                                                <li>1 ladle</li>
                                        <li>Jar lifter and funnel</li>
                                      <li>1 clean cloth</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </section>

                                <section class="recipe-section">
                                    <h3>Ingredients</h3>
                                    <ul class="ingredient-list">
                                        <li>6 cups strawberries, cleaned and hulled</li>
                                      <li>3 tablespoons bottled lemon juice (don't sub with fresh--it's a safety thing)</li>
                                      <li>4 cups lemon juice (bottled, fresh, or a combination)</li>
                                                                            <li>6 cups granulated sugar</li>
                                      
                                    </ul>
                                </section>

                                <section class="recipe-section">
                                    <h3>Instructions</h3>
                                  <h4>ü•Ñ Prep Steps:</h4>
                                  <ol class="step-list">
                                      <li><b>Prep jars and canner:</b> Wash jars, lids, and rings in hot, soapy water. Rinse well. Keep jars hot in a water bath canner. Simmer lids and rings in a separate saucepan (do not boil).</li>
                                      <li><b>Puree strawberries:</b> In a food processor or blender, pur√©e strawberries until smooth. Some seeds may remain, but there should be no chunks.</li>
                                    <li><b> Combine ingredients:</b> Transfer strawberry pur√©e to a large non-reactive saucepan. Add lemon juice and sugar. Stir to combine.</li>
                                    <li><b>Heat mixture:</b> Heat over medium heat until the mixture reaches 190‚Äì200¬∞F. Do not boil. Skim off any foam that forms.</li>
                                    <h4>ü´ô Jar Filling:</h4>
                                      <li><b>Fill jars:
</b> Using a funnel, ladle hot concentrate into jars, leaving ¬º inch headspace.</li>
                                    <li><b>Seal jars:

</b> Wipe rims clean with a damp towel. Place lids on jars and screw bands on until fingertip-tight.</li>
                                                                        
                                    <h4>üî• Water Bath Processing:</h4>
                                    <li><b>Process your jars:</b> Place jars in the boiling water canner, ensuring they‚Äôre fully submerged.

Process for 15 minutes (adjust for altitude if needed)</li>
                                    <li><b>Cool and store:</b>Turn off heat, remove lid, and let jars sit in the canner for 5 minutes. Remove jars and place on a towel-lined surface. Cool undisturbed for 12‚Äì24 hours.</li>
                                    <li><b>Check seals:</b>Press the center of each lid‚Äîif it doesn‚Äôt flex, the jar is sealed. Label and store in a cool, dark place for up to 2 years. </li>
                                    
<b>Refrigerate any unsealed jars and use within 2 weeks.</b>                                  
                                    
</ol>
                                </section>

                               <section class="recipe-section">
    <h3>Notes</h3>
    <ul class="ingredient-list">
      <li><b>Fresh lemon juice is delicious in this recipe,</b> but squeezing four cups of it is extremely tedious.  Try a blend of bottled and fresh. </li>
     
      <li><b>To serve,</b> mix 1 part concentrate with 2 parts water or club soda. Adjust to taste and serve over ice!</li>
    </ul>
</section>
